Plants glabrous or sparsely pubescent proximally; uppermost cauline leaf blades:
        bases cordate-amplexicaul; basal leaf blades: margins 2- or 3-pinnatifid or pinnatisect;
        petals

Fruits obovate to obovate-suborbicular, widest beyond middle; rachises with
        straight, slender to subclavate trichomes; petals absent or rudimentary, 0.3–0.9
        mm;

Fruits orbicular, widest at middle; rachises usually with curved, cylindrical
        trichomes, rarely glabrous; petals usually present, rarely rudimentary, 1–2(–2.5) mm;
        cotyledons usually

Sepals somewhat persistent; fruit valves hirsute (trichomes spreading, mixed with
        smaller ones); petals usually pubescent on outside, rarely glabrescent, with fringed margin;
        racemes compact, subcapitate to cylindrical in

Fruiting pedicels suberect to ascending, subappressed to rachises; fruits (4–)
